Options:

	-deskew   perform deskewing

	-tabtype  indicates the tablature type
	          possible values: 'french', 'italian' ['italian']
	-knnbars  do not recognize bars heuristically but
	          statistically with knn-Classifier
	-abcmusic write music transcription in addition to tabcode
	-tuning <tuning>
	          tuning for music transcription, given from top
	          to bottom. Default is "gdAFCG,"

Usage:
	../../otr_ecolm-2012-08-28/otr_recognize.py [<options>] <infile>
Options:
	-o <abc>        output files basename; extended with .abc and .tab ([basename])
	-d <xml>        training data file ['training/new_phalese.xml']
	-n <num>        number of staff lines (autoguessed when omitted)
	-k <k>          value of k in kNN ([1])
	-v <lev>        verbose level ([1])
	-smooth         perform smoothing
	-deskew         perform deskewing
	-depict         remove pictures
	-despec         remove CC's smaller than staffline_height * 2
	-onlines        fret symbols on the lines
	-ignorecourse0  fret in course0 are ignored
	-split          splits diapasons
	-tabtype        indicates the tablature type
	                possible values: 'french', 'italian' ['french']
	-knnbars        do not recognize bars heuristically but
	                statistically with knn-Classifier
	-abcmusic       write music transcription in addition to tabcode
	-tuning <tuning>
	                tuning for music transcription, given from top
	                to bottom. Default is "gdAFCG,"

Usage:
	../../otr_ecolm-2012-08-28/otr_recognize.py [<options>] <infile>
Options:
	-o <abc>        output files basename; extended with .abc and .tab ([basename])
	-d <xml>        training data file ['']
	-n <num>        number of staff lines (autoguessed when omitted)
	-k <k>          value of k in kNN ([1])
	-v <lev>        verbose level ([1])
	-smooth         perform smoothing
	-deskew         perform deskewing
	-depict         remove pictures
	-despec         remove CC's smaller than staffline_height * 2
	-onlines        fret symbols on the lines
	-ignorecourse0  fret in course0 are ignored
	-split          splits diapasons
	-tabtype        indicates the tablature type
	                possible values: 'french', 'italian' ['french']
	-knnbars        do not recognize bars heuristically but
	                statistically with knn-Classifier
	-abcmusic       write music transcription in addition to tabcode
	-tuning <tuning>
	                tuning for music transcription, given from top
	                to bottom. Default is "gdAFCG,"

	../../otr_ecolm-2012-08-28/otr_recognize.py [<options>] <infile>
Options:
	-o <abc>        output files basename; extended with .abc and .tab ([basename])
	-d <xml>        training data file ['../../ecolm_images/train/K1c11/bianchini_da_crema_merged_class.xml']
	-n <num>        number of staff lines (autoguessed when omitted)
	-k <k>          value of k in kNN ([1])
	-v <lev>        verbose level ([1])
	-smooth         perform smoothing
	-deskew         perform deskewing
	-depict         remove pictures
	-despec         remove CC's smaller than staffline_height * 2
	-onlines        fret symbols on the lines
	-ignorecourse0  fret in course0 are ignored
	-split          splits diapasons
	-tabtype        indicates the tablature type
	                possible values: 'french', 'italian' ['italian']
	-knnbars        do not recognize bars heuristically but
	                statistically with knn-Classifier
	-abcmusic       write music transcription in addition to tabcode
	-tuning <tuning>
	                tuning for music transcription, given from top
	                to bottom. Default is "gdAFCG,"

Tims-MacBook-Pro:ECOLM timc$ cat Recognition/Gardane_3rd_test_run/Gardane_list | while read i; do for j in ecolm_images/png/$i/K*.png; do name=`basename $j`;echo "Splitting $name"; python splitpagesgrey.py -o ecolm_images/Gardane_grey_pages/$i $j; done; done | wc -l
Usage:
	splitpages.py -outdir <outdir> [Options] file1 [file2 ...]
Options:
	-verbose
	      write additional color images for debugging
	-add_t <n>
	      add <n> to the Otsu threshold for darker image
	-shading
	      use shading_subtraction instead of global Otsu threshold for binarization
